sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant Dashboard as Dashboard<br/>HTTPS/443 OAuth
    participant Notebook as Notebook Pod<br/>HTTP/8888 mTLS
    participant Training as Training Operator<br/>HTTP/8443
    participant TrainingPod as Training Job Pod
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2
    participant KServe as KServe Controller<br/>HTTP/8443
    participant ModelCtl as Model Controller<br/>HTTP/8443
    participant Predictor as Predictor Pod<br/>HTTP/8080 mTLS
    participant Gateway as Istio Gateway<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.3
    participant Registry as Model Registry<br/>HTTPS/443 OAuth
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>HTTP/9090

    Note over User,Prometheus: Workflow 1: Interactive Development & Training

    User->>Dashboard: Access dashboard<br/>OAuth Bearer Token
    Dashboard->>Notebook: Create Notebook CR
    Notebook->>Notebook: Pull workbench image<br/>Jupyter + PyTorch CUDA
    User->>Notebook: Develop model code<br/>OAuth authenticated
    Notebook->>S3: Access training data<br/>AWS IAM credentials
    Notebook->>Training: Submit PyTorchJob CR
    Training->>TrainingPod: Launch distributed pods<br/>gang scheduling
    TrainingPod->>S3: Read training data<br/>AWS IAM
    TrainingPod->>TrainingPod: Distributed training<br/>AllReduce gradients
    TrainingPod->>S3: Save model checkpoints<br/>AWS IAM
    TrainingPod-->>Training: Job complete

    Note over User,Prometheus: Workflow 2: Model Deployment & Serving

    User->>Dashboard: Create InferenceService<br/>via UI
    Dashboard->>KServe: Create InferenceService CR<br/>storageUri: s3://models/
    KServe->>KServe: Validate via webhook<br/>mTLS cert auth
    KServe->>Predictor: Create Knative Service<br/>serverless autoscaling
    Predictor->>S3: Download model artifacts<br/>AWS IAM IRSA
    Predictor->>Predictor: Load model into memory<br/>GPU allocation
    KServe->>ModelCtl: Trigger reconciliation<br/>watch event
    ModelCtl->>Gateway: Create VirtualService<br/>Istio API
    ModelCtl->>Gateway: Create OpenShift Route<br/>K8s API
    ModelCtl->>Prometheus: Create ServiceMonitor<br/>metrics scraping
    ModelCtl-->>Dashboard: InferenceService ready

    Note over User,Prometheus: Workflow 3: Inference Request

    User->>Gateway: POST /v1/models/model:predict<br/>Bearer Token (optional)
    Gateway->>Gateway: TLS termination TLS1.3<br/>JWT validation
    Gateway->>Predictor: Forward request<br/>mTLS STRICT
    Predictor->>Predictor: Run inference<br/>GPU accelerated
    Predictor-->>Gateway: Prediction JSON<br/>mTLS encrypted
    Gateway-->>User: HTTPS response<br/>TLS1.3

    Note over User,Prometheus: Workflow 4: Model Registration

    User->>Registry: Register model metadata<br/>OAuth Bearer Token
    Registry->>Registry: Store in PostgreSQL<br/>version, metrics, lineage
    Dashboard->>Registry: Query model info<br/>REST API
    Registry-->>Dashboard: Model metadata JSON
    Dashboard-->>User: Display in UI

    Note over User,Prometheus: Workflow 5: Monitoring

    Predictor->>Prometheus: Expose metrics :8080/metrics<br/>ServiceMonitor
    Gateway->>Prometheus: Expose metrics :15020/stats/prometheus<br/>Istio telemetry
    Dashboard->>Prometheus: Query metrics<br/>PromQL API
    Prometheus-->>Dashboard: Metrics time series
    Dashboard-->>User: Display dashboards
